OL,4,C'broken' young-onset dementia care
OL,5,Csystem
OL,7,FA daughter from Anglesey says failings
OL,8,Fin the care system for people with
OL,9,Fyoung-onset dementia have left her
OL,10,Ffather with #200,000 in outstanding
OL,11,Fcare bills, placing enormous emotional
OL,12,Fand financial strain on her.
OL,14,FErin Thomas, 27, says she trusted
OL,15,Fprofessionals to help her father,
OL,16,FTony, after he was diagnosed with
OL,17,Ffrontotemporal dementia (FTD) at just
OL,18,F52 - the same illness that claimed the
OL,19,Flives of his mother and sister.
