OL,3,CFamily left with #200,000 bill due to
OL,4,C'broken' young-onset dementia care
OL,5,Csystem
OL,7,F"I can confirm all of the actions
OL,8,Fhighlighted within the report have
OL,9,Fbeen completed. Multi-disciplinary
OL,10,Fcolleagues now receive weekly support
OL,11,Fand advice around CHC, including 1:1
OL,12,Ftraining on CHC and s.117 issues. We
OL,13,Fhope this goes some way to satisfying
OL,14,FMiss Thomas's concerns."
OL,16,FErin also lodged a formal complaint to
OL,17,Fher local authority, Anglesey Council
OL,18,Ffor its failure to carry out a
OL,19,Ffinancial assessment for her father
OL,20,Fthat would have checked whether he
OL,21,Fcould afford his care.
